  <title translate="true">Comments/Captions Tab</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Comments/Captions Tab</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Comments/Captions</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true"> </text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">tab is on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Object_Properties_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Object Properties</link><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Object_Properties_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">If you want a caption displayed with an object, check the </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Visible</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> check box in the caption section. If you do not specify the text of the label, the name of the object will be used as the caption. The </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">X and Y offsets</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> specify where the label should appear relative to the first visible vertex of the object. The </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">X and Y offsets</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> are measured in pixels. You can specify a font for the labels. If no font is specified, the default font for the system will be used.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Sometimes an object may be unusual in some way or do something that isn&apos;t obvious. Later on, you may not remember why it is set up the way it is. You can use the Comments field </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Comments/Captions</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> tab to explain features that need explanation.</text></para>
  </body>
</topic>
